<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-11T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-11T19:36:00-05:00" n="1151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.51/262</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-11T18:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 11, 1916—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>475. Reliable information indicates that another decree is in preparation
                            to supplant the Law of Payments decreed by Carranza on September 15.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>